oach rides (without paying), and encountering handsome young ladies and gentlemen (without speaking)-all to return home hours later with whispered joy: "This is a day well spent."This charming edition features elegant and edgy watercolor drawings by Leon Steinmetz and is edited by leading Austen scholar Claudia L. Johnson. In her illuminating afterword, Johnson calls The Beautifull Cassandra "among the most brilliant and polished" of Austen's youthful writings-a precocious work written for the amusement of her family but already anticipating her mature irony, sense of the absurd, gift for parody, and, above all, stylistic mastery.The result is a marvelous edition of a literary treasure that is sure to delight.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aChildren's stories. 0aTeenage girlsvJuvenile fiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aJohnson, Claudia L.1 aSteinmetz, Leon.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060659140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691188928zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691188928423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691188928/original  a978-3-11-060659-1  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK